    "body": "## Goal\n\nImplement the approved adaptive-consensus design so clear evaluations settle efficiently while materially divergent or near-threshold cases receive bounded additional evaluation and unresolved cases end explicitly.\n\n## Context\n\nParent initiative: https://github.com/verdikta/verdikta-roadmap/issues/4\n\nBlocked by the sibling adaptive-consensus and challenge design issue. The current fixed K/M/N/P flow must not be changed until its replacement state machine, economics, invariants, and compatibility behavior are approved.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] High-confidence cases far from the decision threshold complete through the approved fast path.\n- [ ] Material variance and near-threshold results trigger bounded additional arbiter evaluation according to the selected policy.\n- [ ] Persistently weak consensus produces an explicit inconclusive result rather than silently converting disagreement into failure.\n- [ ] The implementation enforces maximum rounds, arbiters, elapsed time, and requester cost.\n- [ ] Commit/reveal, oracle selection, reputation scoring, bonus payments, refunds, and timeout recovery remain correct across every path.\n- [ ] Events and getters expose path, round, variance/confidence inputs, costs, timestamps, and final disposition needed by downstream systems.\n- [ ] Existing callers retain the approved backward-compatible behavior or receive a documented migration path.\n- [ ] Unit, fuzz, invariant, gas, and adversarial tests cover threshold boundaries, repeated disagreement, reentrancy, duplicate responses, insufficient oracles, and accounting conservation.\n- [ ] Deployment, rollback, monitoring, and staging runbooks are complete.\n\n## Validation\n\nRun contract tests and staged evaluations covering fast, variance, near-threshold, inconclusive, timeout, oracle-shortage, and maximum-cost paths. Reconcile every reserved, paid, refunded, and withdrawable balance and confirm no path can finalize twice.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope:\n\n- Dispatcher contracts and libraries\n- Events, getters, tests, deployment, and monitoring\n- Approved adaptive-consensus and inconclusive behavior\n\nOut of scope:\n\n- Per-bounty application UI and bonded challenge UX\n- Unapproved changes to the design\n- Human review operations",
