    "body": "## Goal\n\nProduce an implementable, security-reviewed protocol design for resolving high-confidence, divergent, near-threshold, challenged, and persistently ambiguous evaluations.\n\n## Context\n\nParent initiative: https://github.com/verdikta/verdikta-roadmap/issues/4\n\nThe current `ReputationAggregator` uses a fixed K/M/N/P commit/reveal round and averages a fixed-size closest-response cluster. It does not expand evaluation based on variance, treat near-threshold cases differently, return an explicit inconclusive outcome, or support a bounded economic challenge.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] The design defines measurable fast-path, variance, near-threshold, inconclusive, and challenge conditions.\n- [ ] Additional evaluation is capped by explicit maximum arbiters, rounds, cost, and time.\n- [ ] Per-request policies map Strict, Balanced, Appealable, and application-managed escalation to protocol behavior.\n- [ ] Challenge eligibility, bond sizing, fee allocation, success conditions, replay protection, and finality are specified.\n- [ ] Creators cannot unilaterally override a result after work is submitted.\n- [ ] Commit/reveal secrecy, oracle selection, reputation updates, bonus accounting, refunds, timeout recovery, and liveness are preserved or deliberately revised.\n- [ ] Events and read APIs expose enough information for Verdict Packets and reliability metrics without revealing protected evaluator internals.\n- [ ] Backward compatibility and migration behavior for existing callers are defined.\n- [ ] Threat model, economic-abuse cases, gas/storage analysis, state machine, invariants, and test plan are reviewed and recorded.\n\n## Validation\n\nWalk the state machine against representative agreement, material-variance, near-threshold, timeout, repeated-disagreement, successful-challenge, failed-challenge, oracle-shortage, and maximum-cost cases. Obtain protocol and application review approval before implementation begins.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope:\n\n- Protocol behavior and interfaces\n- Bounded escalation and challenge economics\n- Events, read surfaces, invariants, and migration plan\n\nOut of scope:\n\n- Solidity implementation\n- Application UI\n- Unbounded retries, subjective creator vetoes, or calendar commitments",
